# Project Scope Rules

## Purpose
This project implements a **Stopwatch and Countdown Timer** web application using minimal frontend technologies.

The implementation must follow these constraints:

- The application must be implemented using **vanilla JavaScript**.
- No external frameworks or heavy dependencies are allowed.
- The project must remain **lightweight and easily testable**.

## Allowed Files
Core logic and related assets must remain limited to the following files:

- `stopwatch-ics/index.html` → UI structure
- `stopwatch-ics/script.js` → application logic
- `stopwatch-ics/styles.css` → feature stylesheet
- `stopwatch-ics/script.test.js` → co-located unit tests (and other `*.test.js` in the feature folder)

## UI Reference
The UI must follow the design defined in: res/stopwatch.png

Behavior reference:
https://www.online-stopwatch.com/

## Feature Scope
The application must include:

### Stopwatch Mode
- Start
- Pause
- Continue
- Clear
- Accurate time measurement

### Countdown Mode
- Set duration
- Start countdown
- Pause
- Continue
- Clear

## Non-Goals
The following are explicitly out of scope:
- Frameworks (React, Vue, Angular)
- Backend services
- Build systems
- Package managers
- External UI libraries